Package ohos.wifi.p2p

Class WifiP2pCallback

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.wifi.p2p.WifiP2pCallback

  • public class WifiP2pCallback
extends Object
    Provides callbacks that are invoked to notify the results of Wi-Fi peer-to-peer (P2P) requests.

    Your application can implement the callbacks as needed.

    Since:
    3

      • eventP2pGroup

        public void eventP2pGroup​(WifiP2pGroup group)
        Called when the Wi-Fi P2P group information becomes available.

        Your application can use WifiP2pController#requestP2pInfo(int, WifiP2pCallback) to request the Wi-Fi P2P group information.

        The request ID used to obtain the Wi-Fi P2P group information is WifiP2pController#GROUP_INFO_REQUEST.

        Parameters:
        group - Indicates the Wi-Fi P2P group information, which is defined in WifiP2pGroup.
        Since:
        3

      • eventP2pDevice

        public void eventP2pDevice​(WifiP2pDevice p2pDevice)
        Called when the Wi-Fi P2P device information becomes available.

        Your application can use WifiP2pController#requestP2pInfo(int, WifiP2pCallback) to request the Wi-Fi P2P device information.

        The request ID used to obtain the Wi-Fi P2P device information is WifiP2pController#DEVICE_INFO_REQUEST.

      • eventP2pNetwork

        public void eventP2pNetwork​(WifiP2pNetworkInfo networkInfo)
        Called when the Wi-Fi P2P network information becomes available.

        Your application can use WifiP2pController#requestP2pInfo(int, WifiP2pCallback) to request the Wi-Fi P2P network information.

        The request ID used to obtain the Wi-Fi P2P network information is WifiP2pController#NETWORK_INFO_REQUEST.

        Parameters:
        networkInfo - Indicates the Wi-Fi P2P network information, which is defined in WifiP2pNetworkInfo.
        Since:

      • eventP2pControllerDisconnected

        public void eventP2pControllerDisconnected​()
        Called when the Wi-Fi P2P controller is disconnected.

        After the Wi-Fi P2P controller is disconnected, all Wi-Fi P2P callbacks are deregistered and cannot be used to obtain P2P information.

        Since:
        3
